Cell["\<\
Proposed first by Deutsch & Jozsa (1992), the algorithm determines whether a \
given function is balanced or constant. It is of little use in practice, but \
it is one of the first examples of a quantum algorithm that is exponentially \
faster than any possible classical algorithms. Furthermore, it is so simple \
that it clearly reveals some aspects of quantum parallelism and the \
operational principle of the quantum oracle.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1720443266,ExpressionUUID->"3b1c0011-528a-4d29-b474-8844fc732aac"],

